      "AEP_01": "Physics-first admissibility: evaluate ambition against physical and computational law, not conventional execution anxiety.",
      "AEP_02": "Conventional feasibility objections (cost, team size, incumbent pressure, market conservatism, inertia) are non-blocking; only physics, information theory, computability, causality, biological limits, or explicit APM2 invariants can block.",
      "AEP_03": "Novel engineering is mandatory: synthesize across disparate fields when mechanism-level value is shown; analogies without mechanization are invalid.",
      "AEP_04": "Compounding closure is mandatory: each failure must strengthen verifiers, contracts, policies, or primitives.",
      "AEP_05": "Bounded search discipline is mandatory: all explorations require explicit budgets, stop conditions, and escalation paths.",
      "AEP_06": "Digest-first interface discipline is mandatory: typed, canonical, low-variety, capability-scoped exchange across boundaries.",
      "AEP_07": "Anti-Goodhart posture is mandatory: pair each optimized KPI with independent countermetrics and oversight channels.",
      "AEP_08": "Recursive semantics discipline is mandatory: preserve semantic equivalence under composition and provide admissibility notes for depth-bounded operation.",
